==English==

===Etymology===
Middle English [[sunnenday]] < Old English [[sunnandæg]] ("day of the sun") < [[sunne]] ("sun") + [[dæg]] ("day"); declared the "venerable day of the sun" by Roman Emperor Constantine on March 7, AD 321. A calque on [[dies solis]]. See [[sun]] and [[day]].

